question: Which model uses biometric screening in its ranking process?
prompt:
# CONTEXT #
    This document contains a more detailed description of the model.limeade_lakehouse.gold_stg_metrics_screening_completions model, as well as some specific 
Spark and DBT related configuration for the table. Here is the description: Divides total number of users who've completed a biometric screening against the total registered user population for each customer. It then ranks this value  both against other customers and the book of business customer base as a whole

Table Properties: [delta.checkpoint.writeStatsAsJson=false, delta.checkpoint.writeStatsAsStruct=true]
Statistics: 5285 bytes, 3 rows
Location: dbfs:/mnt/datalake/gold/stg/metrics_screening_completions
Serde Library: org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.lazy.LazySimpleSerDe
InputFormat: org.apache.hadoop.mapred.SequenceFileInputFormat
OutputFormat: org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.HiveSequenceFileOutputFormat

NULL::STRING as question_scale,
    q.is_reverse_score::INTEGER AS reverse_score,
    q.question_weight,
    qr.question_order,
    q.gold_updated_at AS dw_updated_at
FROM `hive_metastore`.`gold_dim`.`questions` q
INNER JOIN `hive_metastore`.`gold_fact`.`user_question_responses_v2` qr
    ON LOWER(qr.question_id) = LOWER(q.question_id)
LEFT JOIN `hive_metastore`.`gold_dim`.`wba_dimensions_v2` gdwd
    ON qr.wba_dimension_id = gdwd.wba_dimension_id
INNER JOIN `hive_metastore`.`gold_dim`.`employers` gde
    ON LOWER(qr.employer_id) = LOWER(gde.employer_id)
INNER JOIN `hive_metastore`.`gold_dim`.`providers` gdp
    ON LOWER(gde.provider_id) = LOWER(gdp.provider_id)
WHERE gdp.legacy__provider_id = 200878 -- UPMC Provider ID
ORDER BY dw_updated_at ASC
View Catalog and Namespace: spark_catalog.default
View Query Output Columns: [question_id, life_area, dimension, question_text, question_type, question_scale, reverse_score, question_weight, question_order, dw_updated_at]
